article.headline: American U. 56, Stony Brook 53
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Nick Hendra scored 16 points and Frane Marcusovic added 13 to help American beat Stony Brook 56-53 on Tuesday night. Garrison Carr had 10 points for the Eagles (4-1), including two free throws with 15 seconds left that sealed the victory. Tommy Brenton scored 13 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for the Patriots (1-3). Chris Martin added 10 points. Dallis Joyner's layup at 17:01 of the second half tied the game at 31. Hendra closed out a 7-1 run on a layup at 12:28 that put American up 38-32. The Patriots got within 54-53 on Brenton's putback with 17 seconds left before Carr hit his two free throws.
